    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>This post I will show you guys how to pass parameter into lookup editor, filter lookup items or change lookup key by parameter’s value</p><p>Demo:</p><img src="/2019/10/17/006-lookup-editor-pass-parameter-and-change-lookup-key/lookup-chang-key-and-pass-parameter.gif"><p>We will need to create a custom lookup editor by typescript, build solution and generate t4 template then use it for your lookup field.</p><p>Demo just has 2 fields, a radio button (Enum type) and dropdown (lookup editor).</p><p>When user changes radio button value, we will reset lookup items corresponding.</p><h3 id="MyLookupEditor-ts"><a href="#MyLookupEditor-ts" class="headerlink" title="MyLookupEditor.ts"></a>MyLookupEditor.ts</h3><script src="//gist.github.com/fb60bfc0c4bbbe82bca8518e27f2c2db.js?file=MyLookupEditor.ts"></script><h3 id="MyEnum"><a href="#MyEnum" class="headerlink" title="MyEnum"></a>MyEnum</h3><script src="//gist.github.com/fb60bfc0c4bbbe82bca8518e27f2c2db.js?file=MyEnum.cs"></script><h3 id="Row-cs"><a href="#Row-cs" class="headerlink" title="Row.cs"></a>Row.cs</h3><script src="//gist.github.com/fb60bfc0c4bbbe82bca8518e27f2c2db.js?file=Row.cs"></script><h3 id="Form-cs"><a href="#Form-cs" class="headerlink" title="Form.cs"></a>Form.cs</h3><script src="//gist.github.com/fb60bfc0c4bbbe82bca8518e27f2c2db.js?file=Form.cs"></script><h3 id="Dialog-ts"><a href="#Dialog-ts" class="headerlink" title="Dialog.ts"></a>Dialog.ts</h3><script src="//gist.github.com/fb60bfc0c4bbbe82bca8518e27f2c2db.js?file=Dialog.ts"></script><p>Done!</p>]]></content>
    
